⚡ Peak State — No-Trigger Protocol (≈30–60 sec)

Think of it as a 3-phase switch: Prime → Rise → Hold

1) PRIME (10–15 sec)
	•	Posture: upright, chest open, chin slightly up
	•	Breath: inhale 4 / exhale 4 × 5–6 cycles
	•	Attention: center of chest

Quiet cue (once or twice):

“Ready.”

You’re just setting the baseline—no forcing.

⸻

2) RISE (10–20 sec)
	•	Keep the same breath, a touch faster
	•	Add ~20% whole-body tension (fists/core), then ease to ~10%
	•	Narrow attention to one point (chest or a spot in your vision)

Paced cue:

“There it is… rising… don’t chase it… let it come.”

Micro-movements (subtle): tiny sway or pulse in the fingers.

👉 You’re catching the first hint of lift and amplifying it a notch.

⸻

3) HOLD (10–25 sec)
	•	Breath shifts to inhale 4 / exhale 6–8
	•	Lift gaze slightly (even eyes closed)
	•	Release most tension; keep a light “tone”

Cue:

“Steady… hold… just enough.”

👉 This converts the spike into a clean, sustained elevation.

⸻

4) EXIT (3–5 sec)
	•	One deep inhale
	•	Look at something solid
	•	Say:

“Back.”

Keeps you in control.

⸻

🧠 Why it works

You’re stacking:
	•	Breath (arousal + control)
	•	Posture (upward emotional bias)
	•	Attention (amplifies signal)
	•	Light tension → release (classic surge pattern)
	•	Language (sets expectation and pacing)

Aligned inputs → predictable output.

