🔧 Make it stronger (without external triggers)

A) “5% Rule”

Don’t hunt a big feeling. Find anything—even 1–2% lift—and push it to 5% more. That’s how it grows reliably.

B) Spatial tilt (fast amplifier)

Assume (don’t visualize hard):
	•	your chest is slightly lifted/expanded, or
	•	the space in front of you is opening upward

This nudges the system toward “up/forward” affect.

C) Rhythm

Add a subtle rhythm (tiny head sway or finger pulse). Rhythm deepens the state without effort.

D) Movement seal

Take 2–3 steps or shift your stance at the end. Movement stabilizes the state.

